content:
View Customer Records in the Salesforce Console

Salesforce automatically creates some records when a chat ends. These records store information about chat customers and their interactions with agents.

Available in: Performance Editions, Unlimited Edition, Enterprise Edition with Service Cloud, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012.

To view customer records:	Read on the record type

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

These records are mostly used internally to provide an audit trail about your customers and their chats with agents. However, you can access these records yourself if you ever need them.

There are a few different types of records you can view in the Salesforce console:

* Chat Session Records
* Chat Visitor Records
* Chat Transcripts
title: Viewing Chat Records in Salesforce Console
